The Aussie word is “CHOOKAS!”
And someone got it right! Such a fun and upbeat expression meaning Good Luck! 
I had to ask Mrs Google for origins and apparently it’s an old vaudeville expression that actors and dancers used to say to wish each other good luck, because If the audience was full, the manager would pay for chicken dinner! Before the show someone would count the audience, if there were a lot, the counter would yell “CHOOKAS”!
The first person to guess was @cnilpirom ✨🥇✨
And she’s the recipient of the first one I’ll make! Can’t wait to see it myself.
Thank you everyone for playing. I tots enjoyed reading your wacky suggestions!

 N xx ✨❤️

Finally! I’ve had this exquisite pair of antique, late Victorian earrings, for a few years now. Heavily influenced by traditional Indian jewelry, they are set in gold with natural pearls and raspberry red paste. The problem was the hooks! They were crazy fish hook style, that had to be inserted backwards and almost always caught painfully in the ear. Ouch! Not anymore. My brilliant jeweler has changed them to post and now they perfectly comfortable and wearable! Pop into the store and try them on for yourself, they are brilliant!
